HEADWORD: Formedon
<hw>For"me*don</hw> <pr>(f⟦ocir⟧r"m⟦esl⟧*d⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OF., fr. Latin. So called because the plaintiff claimed ⟦ldquo⟧by
the form of the gift,⟦rdquo⟧ L. <ets>per formam doni</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A writ of right for a tenant in tail in
case of a discontinuance of the estate tail. This writ has been
abolished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

